description:
Impossible Landing



Aired on 04/13/2012, Narrated by Jonathan Aris



On 19 July 1989, the tail-mounted No.2 engine of United Airlines Flight 232, a McDonnell-Douglas DC-10-10, explodes. By varying engine thrust on the remaining two engines, the pilots manage to crash-land the aircraft at Sioux City, Iowa, saving the lives of 185 of the 296 people on board. Historical note: Attempts by seven different experienced crews in the simulator afterwards, all fail to reach the airport or even get below 10 thousand feet altitude before spinning out of control and crashing.
